+# Step-5 Repair Pass Is Controlled By The Final Step-4 Result Plus The Landed Pro-Side Arithmetic
+
+Status: `VERIFIED` controlling-record inputs with `INFERRED` repair-pass precedence
+
+Step 5 inherits the completed Step-4 verdict as fixed input.
+On the current local record, the controlling repair dossier is
+`missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/steps/step-004/RESULTS.md`
+together with the landed pro-side arithmetic artifact that records the
+friendly maxima on the same frozen ledger.
+
+One intermediate anti-dossier report was narrower about the anti-family
+template and leakage verdicts, but that narrower note is not the controlling
+repair ledger for Step 5.
+Its honest role is provenance and caution for the hostile read, not authority
+to reopen the settled branch record.
+
+The resulting precedence rule for this branch is:
+use the final Step-4 result plus the landed pro-side arithmetic to write the
+repair sheet, and use the intermediate anti-side note only to preserve where
+the hostile failure mode came from.
+
+That keeps the Step-5 repair pass from drifting back into disagreement about
+unfinished intermediate reports while preserving the frozen anti/pro dossier
+that already earned the shortlist.
